<TITLE> War crimes trial panel announced </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Mar 25 (bdnews24.com)  The government has announced war crimes tribunal, investigative agency and prosecution team. Law minister Shafique Ahmed revealed the names of the judges, investigators and prosecutors in a press conference on Thursday. He said their work would start "immediately". The judges include justice Nizamul Haque, justice ATM Fazle Kabir and former district judge Zahirul Ahmed. The seven investigative officers include former additional secretary Abdul Matin, former additional inspector general of police Abdur Rahim, former deputy inspector general of police Kutubur Rahman, Maj ASM Shamsul Arefin, additioanl deputy inspector general of police Mir Shahidul Islam, CID inspectors Nurul Islam and Abdur Razzak Khan. The panel of lawyers are Golam Arif Tipu, the chief prosecutor, Syed Rejaur Rahman, Golam Hasnayen, Zahirul Hoque, Rana Das Gupta, Ziad Al Malum, Syed Haider Ali, Khanaker Abdul Mannan, Mosharraf Hossain Kajal, Nurul Islam Sujan, Sanjida Khanam and Sultan Mahmud Semon. bdne
